  <summary>1/4/1995--Introduced.
Federal Benefit Suspension Act - Amends the Anti-Drug Abuse Act of 1988 to remove discretion from the courts and thus make mandatory the denial of all Federal benefits for a fixed term after a conviction for distribution or possession of a controlled substance.</summary>
